oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Iron Cross medal
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and silver cross pattee-shaped iron medal. The medal is semi-domed with pin-back, which identifies it as a copy. The original Iron Crosses were flat. Marked on top arm of the cross is the Imperial crown; the middle is marked "W" for Wilhelm; and the bottom arm is marked 1914. The reverse is hallmarked 800. The Iron Cross began as a military medal for valor in 1813 and was unique to Prussia. By World War 1914-1918 it was considered a generic German award for valor.
